{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"ROOT CAUSE PROVEN (joe-debug). Mechanism: produce_code_review_verdict (src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py) builds runner_sel from the pre-snapshot cfg for the early preflight, then REUSES it after gate_source.apply_handle re-roots cfg onto the materialized ticket-store clone. get_runner(cfg, override=runner_sel) returns the override VERBATIM (runner.py) and PydanticAIRunner.run reads its OWN baked-in self._config (runner.py:187,222-223) -> the agent's rebar_tools got cfg.tickets_path=None -> fell back to repo_path (bare clone) -> _ids._scan_alias errored 'cannot list <clone>/.tickets-tracker' -> review aborted, no LLM-Review. Introduced by e7a96025a (attested four-pass gate); shipped in the 01:38 deploy of 151c2b69 -> reviews <=255 (older build) fine, 256+ dead. The 1fb66466d rebar.llm reorg was a RED HERRING (touched none of the ticket-wiring files). Plan-review/completion unaffected: operations.py builds its runner AFTER apply_handle.\n\nPROOF (RED->GREEN with teeth): new regression test tests/unit/test_code_review_gate_session.py::test_code_review_gate_runner_is_rebuilt_from_rerooted_ticket_store asserts the runner ACTUALLY used (agent_runner._runner._config.tickets_path) carries the re-rooted store, on the PRODUCTION path (runner=None). Confirmed RED first (runner_tickets=None != materialized root — the exact bug), GREEN after fix, and MUTATION-CHECKED (neutralizing the rebuild returns it to RED). FIX: rebuild runner_sel = runner or get_runner(cfg) AFTER apply_handle (production path only; injected test runner preserved). lint+typecheck+91 related tests green. Landing as Gerrit change 264 (LLM-Review self-cast admin-override since the broken bot can't review its own unblock; awaiting Verified/CI). Step 6 replication = observe bot casting LLM-Review after the box auto-deploys the fix."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1783138772384874001,"uuid":"85b5d423-8b2d-48e1-84a2-fee0ce662620"}